{
  "stem": "9113.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then one day I forgot to wear it, not because I didn't want to wear it, because happened I liked that man, which he passed away, because he was a Jewish friend, Pilsudski.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then my teacher said to me one day when I was not wearing his-- if Hitler would pass away, you would wear this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I said yes, you're right, but I just forgot about it, to do it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Not I didn't-- not-- unconsciously, I forgot.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I didn't-- I didn't want this-- she gave me a few days after this I didn't hear from her.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She always criticized me why I didn't wear that armband.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hitler was-- when we-- when we-- when we were talking in heder with our rabbi, the rabbi used to talk about that, this [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's coming-- a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How should I explain this in English?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's coming-- a very, very bad time, for-- especially for Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's growing-- Hitler's growing a cancer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew about it's going to be bad, but we didn't-- we didn't exactly know it's going to be so bad.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We, like in 1935, '36, '37, we was learning history in the school about the danger of-- of the fascism, in school even, in-- in this-- in Polish school.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And our teacher explained to us that he wants to conquer the world.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, I didn't know about the world.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I knew only about Europe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't know of America at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We-- we-- we were very frightened, but we had no-- to go to Israel, I couldn't dream about it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My older brother went for a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know-- you know-- how to explain this?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He wanted to go to Israel illegally, then he has to train himself in a little town.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
